The paper deals with the transmission of multiple camera views for interactive navigation in 3D scenes, which involves multimedia (MM) processing and network infrastructure (NI) optimization. The paper also discusses the synthesis of virtual views, which is related to computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR). Finally, the paper proposes an optimization problem and algorithms to solve it, which is related to information theory (IT).
